               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221204-147-person1290">
                  WILLIAM 
                  TARRANT
               <interp inst="t18221204-147-person1290" type="surname" value="TARRANT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-147-person1290" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-147-person1290" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a journeyman carpenter, and live at Hoxton. On Sunday afternoon, the 1st of December, I saw the prisoner going in a direction from where I had left my tools on the Saturday afternoon about three o'clock. He had a basket of tools; he said they were his own. I found a mallet and gauge of mine, which I had left in an unfinished house the night before, with two planes and some chisels, which Coleby and Willis claimed.</p>
               <p>
            
