            . I was work with Coleby. I left a plane, which I afterwards found at Worship-street. I left it on Friday morning.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221204-147-person1293">
                  JAMES 
                  HANDLEY
               <interp inst="t18221204-147-person1293" type="surname" value="HANDLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-147-person1293" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-147-person1293" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I was passing at the time the prisoner was stopped by Tarrant. I took the basket of tools from him. He wished to give them up, saying he had made a bad job of it, but supposed he should not be hung.</p>
               <p>(Property poduced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. It rained very hard on Sunday afternoon. I went into a house for shelter; the door was open, and I took some of the tools up to carry them somewhere to secure them, being a carpenter myself. I found the rest by the side of a house.</p>
